    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory allocation error handling in static mobility generator\n\n### Summary\nThe `start_static_generator()` function in the OMG mobility module was not properly handling memory allocation failures, which could lead to segmentation faults when the system is under memory pressure. Additionally, the function had an inconsistent interface compared to other generator functions in the codebase.\n\nThis fix addresses these issues by:\n1. Changing the function signature to return an integer status code\n2. Adding proper error checking for memory allocation failures\n3. Ensuring consistent error handling across all generator functions\n4. Adding proper cleanup when allocation fails\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/static.c`: Changed return type from void to int, added error checking for node and mobility structure allocation, added proper return values\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/static.h`: Updated function signature and documentation to reflect return value\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/omg.c`: Updated caller to check return value and log errors appropriately\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/rwalk.h`: Updated documentation to reflect correct return type\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/rwp.h`: Updated documentation to reflect correct return type\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/steadystaterwp.h`: Added missing function documentation\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/trace.h`: Added missing function documentation\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Run the OMG mobility generator with static node configuration\n2. Under memory pressure or when malloc fails, the function would crash instead of returning an error\n3. The inconsistent interface made it difficult to handle errors properly in the calling code\n\nThe fix ensures that allocation failures are properly reported and that all generator functions have a consistent interface for error handling.\n"
}